schema.name: comparison_group_id
schema.purpose: Logical key that groups runs into one composed workstream comparison.

schema.name: source_bucket
schema.purpose: Where the source report lives; helps provenance and filtering.

schema.name: report_path
schema.purpose: Path to the source workflow-report JSON used for this row.

schema.name: run_id
schema.purpose: Unique workflow execution identifier.

schema.name: papers_dir
schema.purpose: Input paper path(s) processed by the run.

schema.name: started_at
schema.purpose: Workflow start timestamp.

schema.name: finished_at
schema.purpose: Workflow end timestamp.

schema.name: duration_sec
schema.purpose: Run duration in seconds for cost/latency comparison.

schema.name: chat_model
schema.purpose: Primary LLM used by the run.

schema.name: embedding_model
schema.purpose: Embedding model used for retrieval/chunk similarity.

schema.name: report_question_set
schema.purpose: Question set mode (structured|agentic|both|none).

schema.name: report_question_count
schema.purpose: Number of structured/agentic report question records emitted.

schema.name: agentic_status
schema.purpose: Top-level status for agentic stage.

schema.name: index_status
schema.purpose: Top-level status for index stage.

schema.name: index_reason_or_error
schema.purpose: Failure/skipped reason to diagnose differences.

schema.name: report_store_status
schema.purpose: Whether report was stored to Postgres.

schema.name: prep_corpus_hash
schema.purpose: Fingerprint of corpus content; validates same input set.

schema.name: config_hash
schema.purpose: Effective configuration hash; validates run comparability.

schema.name: confidence_mean
schema.purpose: Mean confidence score across structured questions.

schema.name: confidence_labels
schema.purpose: Label distribution summary for quick quality profile.

schema.name: final_answer_preview
schema.purpose: Truncated synthesis preview for side-by-side semantic comparison.
